19;s:103:"You dont need to lubricate the tracks but ensuring theyre clean is essential to your doors functioning.";i:20;s:84:"Spray down the garage torsion springs that lift your garage door day in and day out.";i:21;s:77:"Again you want to only lubricate them enough that they move better without a.";i:22;s:22:"Teflon Silicone Spray.";i:23;s:37:"This leaves Teflon or Silicone spray.";i:24;s:94:"Both of these are sprayed onto the rollers inside the track and on the hinges across the door.";i:25;s:133:"The spray works its way into the rollers and hinges and enables smooth operation minimizes friction and frees the door up to operate.";i:26;s:84:"Focus on the springs as well because these are likely the cause of your loud noises.";i:27;s:111:"These need to be lubricated often because this helps to reduce the amount of friction thats in the steel coils.";i:28;s:92:"To do this just put a little bit of it on the springs making sure that you start at the top.";i:29;s:160:"To lubricate your garage door be sure to spray the hinges the rollers the tracks the door spring and any gears or chains that your garage door opener might use.";i:30;s:19:"How often should I.";i:31;s:71:"Follow the step-by-step directions below to lubricate your garage door.";i:32;s:75:"Close the garage door and turn off the power to the opener if you have one.";i:33;s:84:"Wipe the inside and outside of the tracks with a damp rag to remove dirt and debris.";i:34;s:124:"Never use a lubricant on the tracks since this makes it harder for the rollers to move and forces the opener to work harder.";i:35;s:101:"Regular garage door lubrication will keep your garage door system running smooth and quiet for years.";i:36;s:118:"If your garage door isnt properly lubricated it can lead to permanent damage and shorten the life of your garage door.";i:37;s:165:"Ernie Bernarducci VP of Research and Development at WD-40 Company demonstrates how to use 3-IN-ONE Garage Door lubricant to keep your garage door operating properly.";i:38;s:148:"Instead of hurrying to lubricate the garage door when it is getting sticky of making noises you should first clean the garage door track thoroughly.";i:39;s:99:"All it takes is some simple wiping of the inside of the garage door track using a clean damp cloth.";i:40;s:96:"Once the inside of the track is clean wipe it off with a dry cloth and then apply the lubricant.";i:41;s:69:"Using a ladder unplug the garage door from the outlet on the ceiling.";i:42;s:35:"Vacuum out the garage doors tracks.";i:43;s:26:"With a damp rag wipe down.";}}